  "text": "Willing participants undergo a percutaneous skeletal muscle biopsy as previously described [CITATION_1] . Samples are collected under 2% lidocaine local anesthetic using a six-gauge needle with suction applied. Samples are snap frozen in liquid nitrogen and stored at À80 C for later analysis. Participants currently taking antiplatelet or anti-coagulant medications, with conditions which reduce wound healing, or with a known allergy to lidocaine are excluded from the biopsy procedure.",
